HEADWORD: Antihelix
<hw>An`ti*he"lix</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The curved elevation of the cartilage of the ear, within or in
front of the helix. See <er>Ear</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antihemorrhagic</ent>⟦br⟧
